						<div class="postbody">Is it really a low-pass filter on PA12 with a period longer than one fetch, or is it just to deglitch the signal? I ask because PA12 is one of the inputs to the bankswitching function (the others being PA11 and PA10). So wouldn't a low-pass filter on PA12 also affect bankswitching? At this point, I'd propose a decap and photomicrograph of the MMC3 IC so that we can see exactly what's going on inside that chip.</div>

